import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['date'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['wounds'], label='Wounds')
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['other'], label='Other')
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['disease'], label='Disease')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Cases')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the trend of wounds, other and disease over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['wounds', 'other', 'disease'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist([data['wounds'], data['other'], data['disease']], bins=10, label=['wounds', 'other', 'disease'])
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wounds, other and disease?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['wounds'], data['other'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between wounds and other?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby(pd.Grouper(key='date', freq='M')).sum()
    data = data.div(data.sum(axis=1), axis=0)
    data.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    plt.title('What is the percentage of wounds, other and disease cases by month?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Cases', loc='center left', bbox_to_anchor=(1.0, 0.5))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['date'])
    data = data.groupby('date').mean().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['date'], data['wounds'], color='red', label='Wounds')
    plt.bar(data['date'], data['other'], color='blue', label='Other')
    plt.bar(data['date'], data['disease'], color='green', label='Disease')
    plt.axhline(y=data.mean().mean(), color='black', linestyle='--', label='Average')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average number of wounds, other and disease cases per day?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
